  <span id="freeText4045999523297027487" style="display:none">One of my favorite books. Really gorgeous prose. The What and the Why are definitely secondary to the How in this one. I can see why some people might think there is something lacking in plot or character development, but I think there's just enough for the lack not to matter in the context of how glorious it is just to dwell in Mendelsohn's moments. </span>
