    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1255898374" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1255898374" />
    <a title="Tara ~ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18256476-tara"><img alt="Tara ~ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603120117p2/18256476.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1255898374?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara ~ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara ~ " href="/user/show/18256476-tara">Tara ~ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18256476-tara?shelf=our-book-club">our-book-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1255898374" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11774069707679814240">What lovely writing there is here. You really experience everything that Earhart and her navigator, Fred Noonan see, feel, taste and hear. The sounds of the gulls, the taste of the seaspray, the beating of the hot tropical sun. You can hear her thoughts and start to understand how her mind works, all the things that made her who she was. Although her fate is shrouded in mystery to this day, there is a sense of closure, of atonement/reconciliation and acceptance of what happened to her through he</span>
  <span id="freeText11774069707679814240" style="display:none">What lovely writing there is here. You really experience everything that Earhart and her navigator, Fred Noonan see, feel, taste and hear. The sounds of the gulls, the taste of the seaspray, the beating of the hot tropical sun. You can hear her thoughts and start to understand how her mind works, all the things that made her who she was. Although her fate is shrouded in mystery to this day, there is a sense of closure, of atonement/reconciliation and acceptance of what happened to her through her character in this slim book. I really enjoyed reading it and regret having put off doing so for nearly twenty years.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11774069707679814240" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


