<div id="review_11898685" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/11898685" />
    <a title="Shannon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65207-shannon"><img alt="Shannon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465962504p2/65207.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/11898685?book_show_action=true">Jan 07, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shannon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shannon" href="/user/show/65207-shannon">Shannon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">people who can tolerate a book of fiction based on facts</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer11898685" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13531935943366532619">Pretty good. I don&apos;t understand what all the praise on the cover was about, though, as it wasn&apos;t THAT good.<br/><br/>The constant perspective changes (from first to third person), while clearly a styalistic choice, really annoyed me. <br/><br/>All the things leading up to Amelia&apos;s and Noonan&apos;s flight (ie, the first half of the book) I found vaguely boring.<br/><br/>The second half of the book, on the island, I found very interesting. Good, even. I think Jane Mehndelson&apos;s other book, Innocence, is far better, though. </span>
  <span id="freeText13531935943366532619" style="display:none">Pretty good. I don't understand what all the praise on the cover was about, though, as it wasn't THAT good.<br /><br />The constant perspective changes (from first to third person), while clearly a styalistic choice, really annoyed me. <br /><br />All the things leading up to Amelia's and Noonan's flight (ie, the first half of the book) I found vaguely boring.<br /><br />The second half of the book, on the island, I found very interesting. Good, even. I think Jane Mehndelson's other book, Innocence, is far better, though. </span>
